<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uliubaijadetiger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liubai Jadetiger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast Prince</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/12/02 9:42:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=525.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tchalla.net/BenIcon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Savage Lord's Eitchatka changed</span><hr size=1> The simple (and good) reason that they added monks to the list of usable classes is to decrease the chances that it will rot on a raid.<br>
<br>
Having a bst-only item drop on a raid is great if you're the only beastlord there and you get to loot it.<br>
<br>
It sucks if you spent a bunch of time prepping to kill a major mob that isn't overly common, and after all that, one of the drops is something that no one on the raid can use.<br>
<br>
That is something that can happen with any class, but it can especially happen with bst-only items because a significant number of high-level raiding guilds don't have enough beastlords to ensure that one will always be on a given raid.<br>
<br>
If you want a real culprit for this problem, blame no drop items.  If items from uber mobs were tradeable, then guilds could vault them for contributing members who unfortunately may have missed a given raid or they could trade them with other guilds for equivalent uber loot.<br>
<br>
Verant has always been against this idea, because of the fear that people would twink lowbies with Vulak loot or something.  However, with the ability to restrict items by level, it would seem that the need for no drop is drastically diminished.  If you don't want people twinking level 10 beastlords with Savage Lords' Eitchakas, then make it so that they can't equip them until 58+, for example (which is apparently what they have done).<br>
<br>
Also, this would make equipping a guild much less of a nightmare.  Now, if super_duper_BP drops, guilds have a tendency to make sure that the MA gets it.  But if the MA is already wearing a Vindi BP, then the Vindi gets banked and is essentially wasted.  If items were tradeable (yet level restricted), then that same guild could upgrade the MA with the super_duper_BP and pass down the Vindi BP to someone else who needed it.  <br>
<br>
Thus, every single encounter upgrades the guild at a more efficient rate.  When you've got 70+ people to worry about, each wanting things on multiple slots, and an uber mob that you have to compete with other guilds to even attempt, the 8-10 items that you get per kill should give more bang for the buck.  You want your monks/rogues/etc. to have the best weapons possible for DPS, but when your monk upgrades to primal/glowing acrylia, there's no reason that he shouldn't be able to pass down his priceless to the monk with an SoS.<br>
<br>
Two happy monks &gt; one happy monk.<br>
<br>
This is an idea whose time has come, with more and more guilds capable of doing high level zones and ridiculous competion not only for the mobs in that zone, but for the ones who lead to access to the zone (i.e., key quest mobs).  Yet I doubt that we will ever see it. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90287 target=_blank><img src=http://www.tchalla.net/BenPortrait.jpg /></a><br>
